Bizspace Spotlight
        





 Sponsor Listing 



                    Property Spotlight: Class A Office Space | Clear Lake                




See All Bizspace Properties



 
 











 Enlarge





                The Sterling Group acquired Stetson Building Products Inc. for its new Construction… more 

                TBJ File Photo            








 



The Sterling Group, a Houston-based private equity firm, has acquired the third company for its recently formed Construction Supply Holdings business.
Sterling acquired management-owned Stetson Building Products Inc. for an undisclosed amount, according to a Jan. 2 press release. Des Moines, Iowa-based Stetson joins St. Paul, Minnesota-based Brock White Company LLC and Phoenix-based Border Construction Specialities LLC, both of which Sterling acquired in November to create Construction Supply Holdings.













 Enlarge






                            The Sterling Group acquired Stetson Building Products Inc. for its new Construction… more 
TBJ File Photo










 


Construction Supply Holdings distributes construction materials, accessories and tools, primarily for professional concrete and masonry contractors in the U.S. and Canada. Stetson, a construction supply distributor, enhances Construction Supply Holdings’ technical expertise in the reinforcing steel fabrication and form rental categories.




Stetson has nine branches and a distribution center across Iowa, Illinois, Nebraska and Wisconsin, while Brock White and Border have branches in western Canada, the Upper Midwest and the Southwest. Combined, Construction Supply Holdings has 48 branches with 750 employees and serves nearly 25,000 customers.
"Sterling has a vision to build a best-in-class distribution business, and the entire Stetson team is excited about being a part of that success," Marte Cook, president of Stetson, said in the release. "The opportunity to join forces with Brock White and Border made Sterling the ideal partner for the next phase of our company's growth."
Sterling targets controlling interests in basic manufacturing, distribution and industrial services companies. The firm targets middle-market companies, with enterprise values ranging from $100 million to $750 million. It ranked No. 3 on Houston Business Journal’s Largest Houston-Area Venture Capital & Private Equity Firms List in October, based on its $2.31 billion in assets under management. Currently, Sterling reports more than $2.2 billion of assets under management.

Olivia Pulsinelli is the senior web editor for the Houston Business Journal's award-winning website. Follow her on Twitter for more.











 






